From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] debug: k_msleep between WR_TRACE printks (CDC backpressure)

Even with led_start() bypassed (patch 0025: err = 0), main goes silent
after WR_TRACE 2a_pre_led_start. Two adjacent printks with only
'err = 0' between them — there is nothing in main to hang on. So the
silence is from CDC ACM TX backpressure: the TX ring fills, printk
blocks waiting for the host to drain.

Confirm by inserting k_msleep(100) before 2b. If 2b lands after the
sleep, backpressure is the cause and we know to widen the CDC ring
or add pacing.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
@@ -160,6 +160,7 @@ int main(void)
     printk("WR_TRACE: 2a_pre_led_start\n");

     /* patch 0025: bypass led_start() to isolate hang */
+    k_msleep(100);
     err = 0;
     printk("WR_TRACE: 2b_post_led_start err=%d\n", err);
     if (err) {
@@ -169,11 +170,14 @@ int main(void)

     printk("WR_TRACE: 3_pre_led_seq\n");
     // Run the boot LED sequence
+    k_msleep(50);
     boot_led_sequence();
+    k_msleep(50);
     printk("WR_TRACE: 4_post_led_seq\n");

     // Initialize watchdog early to catch any freezes during boot
     printk("WR_TRACE: 4a_pre_wdt\n");
+    k_msleep(50);
     err = watchdog_init();
     printk("WR_TRACE: 4b_post_wdt err=%d\n", err);
     if (err) {
